What is server ?
-----------------

A server "serves" data or services (like websites, files, emails or databases) to users or devices that request it.

Example:

	.Web server -> serves websites (e.g., Apache, Nginx)
	.Database server -> stores and manages data (e.g., MySQL, Postgres, microsoft etc)
	.File Server -> stores and shares files between servers
	.Mail server -> handles emails (e.g., Microsoft Exchange)
	.Application Server -> runs business logics 

Server Hardware Components:
---------------------------
	.CPU (brain of the server, exutes instructions and processes data)
	eg: Intel
	.RAM (stores data temporarily)
	.Motherboard (this is main circuit board that connects all components)
	.NIC
	.Storage Drives:(HDD-Hard disk Drive/SSD-Solid state drive)
	.Cooling system
	
Server software components:
---------------------------
	.OS(Operating systems) - 
		Linux distrubtions (ubuntu, redhat, centos, fedora, kali 600+)
		windows (by micro soft)
		Mac OS (Apple)
	
	The OS provides:
		.File system management
		.Process and memory managment
		.Network communication
		.security and user management
		
Type of server:			Example Software:			Function:
-------------------------------------------------------------
Web server				Apache, Nginx				Host websites
Database server			MySQL, PostreSQL			Stores and manages data
File server				samba, FTP, NFS				shares files and folders
Mail server				Microsoft, Postfix			sends and recives emails
Application server		Tomcat, WebLogic			Runs business applications
DNS server				BIND, Microsoft DNS			Resolves domain names		
		
		
A server Powerful with hardware + software desinged to provide contineous, reliable to clients

	.Hardware gives performance, reliability, and capacity
	.Software gives functionality, management and security
	
		

